I am a student and resident of THS/Teaneck and honestly, I believe that all 
of you blaming the teachers, insulting the parents, calling the students in 
this predicament criminals should really read this:
1) The media exaggerates everything, especially ones run by commercials and 
ratings (CBS, News 12, PIX 11, etc.)
2) The original prank was to tepee the school with toilet tissue and 
balloons. Possibly Vaseline some places, I am not exactly sure, they put 
Vaseline on door knobs a few years back though. However, it got out of hand 
when more people (many people who weren't even SENIORS) wanted to take it 
to the next level by urinating, vandalizing, and other criminal-like 
activities.
3) SOME KIDS ARE NOT SHELTERED! Yes, we live in a rich county. Yes, there a 
those people who have parents that make a lot of money. However, we are not 
an extremely rich community at all! You are definitely confusing us with 
Ridgewood and Old Tappan (which are extremely rich and sheltered 
communities and most of the kids there are on drugs.) We have a diverse 
population, and actually the Teaneck district is the first IN THE NATION to 
VOLUNTARILY vote for integrated schools 50 years. We are actually 
celebrating that event today :)
4) I know some of the people who were apart of this prank who DID NOT MEAN 
for it to get out of hand. A lot of them are good young adults with bright 
futures.
All I am saying is that do not rely on facts because they tend to 
exaggerate, it is not the parents fault it is the children's fault, don't 
blame the teachers because they cannot monitor our plans and conversations 
every five seconds, this does not deserve nationwide attention (it really 
doesn't), this is just a case of "good kids, bad decisions." As a member of 
the Teaneck community, I and the rest of Teaneck would like if you would 
stop bashing our community and generalizing everyone as awful, stupid 
animals. Thank you, and have a nice day.﻿
